WHAT IS CLOUD
----------------

*Cloud means using the internet to store data and run applications instead of keeping them only on your own computer.
*Itâ€™s like renting computers, storage, and software from companies (like AWS, Azure, Google Cloud).
*You can access it anytime, anywhere using the internet.
*No need to buy and maintain big servers, the cloud provider manages everything.
ğŸ‘‰ In short: Cloud = Computers, storage, and software available on the internet.

EXAMPLE

*Think about Google Drive or Gmail.
*You donâ€™t keep your emails or files only on your laptop.
*They are stored in the cloud (Googleâ€™s servers).
*You can open them on any phone or computer anywhere in the world, just by logging in.
ğŸ‘‰ Same way, companies use cloud services (like AWS, Azure, GCP) to store data, run apps, and manage servers without buying big machines.


